      <hedline>
        <hl1>Half-Gone, But Not Forgotten</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By MARIANNE ROHRLICH</byline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Half-used onions are often the orphans of the refrigerator, languishing in the corners of crispers. But now they -- and their grapefruit and tomato cousins -- have their own cozy plastic containers called Forget-Me-Nots. They are five inches across and come in blue or green, with a handy hook so they can hang on a refrigerator shelf; $10 a pair from Tupperware: www.tupperware.com or (888) 887-9273.</p>
        <p>MARIANNE ROHRLICH</p>
      </block>
